### Starting from Different Positions

Entities with the same velocity but staggered starting points:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((v 100))
    (world
      (entity 'a
              (placement (+ 0 (* t v)) 150)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 7 '#xF1948A)))
      (entity 'b
              (placement (+ 80 (* t v)) 240)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 7 '#xF1948A)))
      (entity 'c
              (placement (+ 160 (* t v)) 330)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 7 '#xF1948A))))))
```

[VISUAL: Three pink circles moving in parallel, evenly spaced horizontally and diagonally staggered vertically. They maintain constant separation.]

Same velocity, different starting positions. The formation moves rigidly.

