### Velocity and Spacing

Spacing a stream of entities in time versus spacing them in distance:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((v 90)
        (interval 0.3))
    (world
      (entity 'first
              (placement (* t v) 200)
              (shapes
                (rect -6 -6 12 12 '#x5DADE2)))
      (entity 'second
              (placement (* (- t interval) v) 200)
              (shapes
                (rect -6 -6 12 12 '#x5DADE2)))
      (entity 'third
              (placement (* (- t (* 2 interval)) v) 200)
              (shapes
                (rect -6 -6 12 12 '#x5DADE2))))))
```

[VISUAL: Three blue squares in a horizontal line, evenly spaced, all moving right at the same speed. The spacing is maintained by the time offset.]

Each entity starts 0.3 seconds after the previous one. At velocity 90, they maintain a spatial separation of 27 pixels.

