### Velocity Ratios

Two entities with velocities in a simple ratio (2:1) produce predictable relationships:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((x1 (* t 60))
        (x2 (* t 120)))
    (world
      (entity 'half-speed
              (placement x1 180)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 10 '#xAED6F1)))
      (entity 'full-speed
              (placement x2 300)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 10 '#x2874A6))))))
```

[VISUAL: A light blue circle and a dark blue circle. The dark one moves twice as fast. At t=0.5, the light circle is at x=30, the dark at x=60.]

Velocity ratio 2:1 means the dark circle covers twice the distance in the same time.

---

A 3:2 ratio:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((v-base 80)
        (x1 (* t (* v-base 2)))
        (x2 (* t (* v-base 3))))
    (world
      (entity 'two
              (placement x1 220)
              (shapes
                (rect -8 -8 16 16 '#xF8B400)))
      (entity 'three
              (placement x2 260)
              (shapes
                (rect -8 -8 16 16 '#xCA6F1E))))))
```

[VISUAL: Two squares, one yellow and one orange. The orange square moves 1.5× as fast as the yellow.]

