### Diagonal Symmetry

Two entities moving in opposite diagonal directions, mirrored velocities:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((vx 100)
        (vy 80))
    (world
      (entity 'down-right
              (placement (+ 100 (* t vx)) (+ 100 (* t vy)))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 9 '#x48C9B0)))
      (entity 'up-left
              (placement (+ 380 (* t (- vx))) (+ 380 (* t (- vy))))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 9 '#xAF7AC5))))))
```

[VISUAL: A teal circle descending from upper-left and a lavender circle ascending from lower-right, both moving diagonally in opposite directions.]

Symmetric velocities: one moves (+vx, +vy), the other (−vx, −vy). They cross paths at the center.

