### Radial Motion

Entities moving outward from a common center at constant speeds:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((cx 240)
        (cy 240)
        (speed 70))
    (world
      (entity 'north
              (placement cx (- cy (* t speed)))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 6 '#xE74C3C)))
      (entity 'east
              (placement (+ cx (* t speed)) cy)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 6 '#x3498DB)))
      (entity 'south
              (placement cx (+ cy (* t speed)))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 6 '#x2ECC71)))
      (entity 'west
              (placement (- cx (* t speed)) cy)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 6 '#xF39C12))))))
```

[VISUAL: Four colored dots radiating outward from the center of the canvas along the cardinal directions—north (red), east (blue), south (green), west (orange)—at equal speeds.]

Radial expansion at 70 px/s.

---

Radial motion at eight directions:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((cx 240)
        (cy 240)
        (r (* t 60)))
    (world
      (entity 'd0
              (placement (+ cx r) cy)
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333)))
      (entity 'd45
              (placement (+ cx (* r 0.707)) (- cy (* r 0.707)))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333)))
      (entity 'd90
              (placement cx (- cy r))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333)))
      (entity 'd135
              (placement (- cx (* r 0.707)) (- cy (* r 0.707)))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333)))
      (entity 'd180
              (placement (- cx r) cy)
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333)))
      (entity 'd225
              (placement (- cx (* r 0.707)) (+ cy (* r 0.707)))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333)))
      (entity 'd270
              (placement cx (+ cy r))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333)))
      (entity 'd315
              (placement (+ cx (* r 0.707)) (+ cy (* r 0.707)))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x333333))))))
```

[VISUAL: Eight dark gray circles expanding outward from the center in a symmetric starburst pattern, each at 45° intervals.]

Uniform radial velocity produces a perfect expanding ring.

---


### Circular Paths at Constant Angular Velocity

An entity orbiting a center point at constant angular speed:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let* ((cx 240)
         (cy 240)
         (radius 100)
         (angular-velocity 2.0)
         (theta (* t angular-velocity))
         (x (+ cx (* radius (cos theta))))
         (y (+ cy (* radius (sin theta)))))
    (world
      (entity 'orbiter
              (placement x y)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 8 '#x9B59B6))))))
```

[VISUAL: A purple circle tracing a circular orbit around the center of the canvas, completing one full revolution every π seconds.]

Angular velocity 2.0 rad/s. The **linear speed** along the orbit is `radius × angular-velocity = 100 × 2 = 200` px/s.

---

Two entities orbiting at different radii, same angular velocity:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let* ((cx 240)
         (cy 240)
         (omega 1.5)
         (theta (* t omega))
         (r1 60)
         (r2 120))
    (world
      (entity 'inner
              (placement (+ cx (* r1 (cos theta)))
                         (+ cy (* r1 (sin theta))))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 6 '#x1ABC9C)))
      (entity 'outer
              (placement (+ cx (* r2 (cos theta)))
                         (+ cy (* r2 (sin theta))))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 6 '#xE67E22))))))
```

[VISUAL: Two circles orbiting the center on concentric circular paths. The inner (teal) circle's orbit is tighter; the outer (orange) circle's orbit is wider. They remain aligned radially, sweeping out the same angle at the same time.]

Same angular velocity, different radii → different linear speeds.

---


### Counter-Rotating Orbits

Two entities orbiting in opposite directions:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let* ((cx 240)
         (cy 240)
         (radius 90)
         (omega 1.2)
         (theta1 (* t omega))
         (theta2 (* t (- omega))))
    (world
      (entity 'clockwise
              (placement (+ cx (* radius (cos theta1)))
                         (+ cy (* radius (sin theta1))))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 7 '#x5DADE2)))
      (entity 'counter
              (placement (+ cx (* radius (cos theta2)))
                         (+ cy (* radius (sin theta2))))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 7 '#xEC7063))))))
```

[VISUAL: A blue circle and a red circle orbiting the center in opposite directions on the same circular path. They meet and pass each other twice per revolution.]

One rotates with angular velocity +1.2, the other −1.2. Relative angular velocity: 2.4 rad/s.

