### Measuring Instantaneous Speed

Two entities, one with constant speed, the other with varying speed, sampled at a single frame:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let* ((t0 0.5)
         (x-const (* t0 100))
         (vx-var (* 100 (cos (* 6.28318 t0))))
         (vy-var (* 100 (sin (* 6.28318 t0))))
         (x-var (* t0 100))
         (y-var 0)
         (speed-const 100)
         (speed-var (sqrt (+ (* vx-var vx-var) (* vy-var vy-var)))))
    (world
      (entity 'const
              (placement x-const 200)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 8 '#x27AE60)))
      (entity 'var
              (placement x-var (+ 280 y-var))
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 8 '#xE74C3C))))))
```

[VISUAL: A green circle at (50, 200) and a red circle at (50, 280). At this instant, the green's speed is exactly 100 px/s; the red's speed (from its varying velocity) is also ≈100 px/s, but will change in the next frame.]

Snapshot at t=0.5. The green entity has constant velocity; the red's velocity varies over time (shown frozen here).

---


### Relative Velocity in Two Dimensions

Two entities moving at different velocities; compute their relative velocity:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let* ((vx1 60)
         (vy1 40)
         (vx2 -30)
         (vy2 80)
         (x1 (+ 150 (* t vx1)))
         (y1 (+ 150 (* t vy1)))
         (x2 (+ 330 (* t vx2)))
         (y2 (+ 100 (* t vy2)))
         (rel-vx (- vx2 vx1))
         (rel-vy (- vy2 vy1))
         (rel-speed (sqrt (+ (* rel-vx rel-vx) (* rel-vy rel-vy)))))
    (world
      (entity 'a
              (placement x1 y1)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 8 '#x1ABC9C)))
      (entity 'b
              (placement x2 y2)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 8 '#xE67E22))))))
```

[VISUAL: A teal circle and an orange circle drifting in different directions. Their paths will cross or diverge depending on their relative velocity.]

Relative velocity of B with respect to A: `(−90, 40)`. Relative speed ≈ 98.5 px/s.

---


### Wave Interference: Two Traveling Waves

Two entities oscillating left-right at different frequencies, creating a visual beat pattern:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let* ((f1 1.0)
         (f2 1.3)
         (amp 80)
         (x1 (+ 200 (* amp (sin (* 6.28318 f1 t)))))
         (x2 (+ 280 (* amp (sin (* 6.28318 f2 t))))))
    (world
      (entity 'wave1
              (placement x1 200)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 7 '#x3498DB)))
      (entity 'wave2
              (placement x2 280)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 7 '#x9B59B6))))))
```

[VISUAL: A blue circle and a purple circle oscillating horizontally around their respective center points at slightly different frequencies. They periodically align and drift out of phase.]

The beat frequency is |f2 − f1| = 0.3 Hz. The circles align every 1/0.3 ≈ 3.3 seconds.

---


### Entity Following a Leader (Simple Lag)

One entity follows another with a time delay:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let* ((lag 0.4)
         (t-follower (max 0 (- t lag)))
         (x-leader (+ 100 (* t 90)))
         (x-follower (+ 100 (* t-follower 90))))
    (world
      (entity 'leader
              (placement x-leader 200)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 9 '#xE74C3C)))
      (entity 'follower
              (placement x-follower 260)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 9 '#xF1948A))))))
```

[VISUAL: A bright red circle leading and a pale red circle following 0.4 seconds behind. The follower traces the same path but is always offset in time.]

Lag creates a trailing effect. At constant velocity, the spatial separation is `lag × velocity = 0.4 × 90 = 36` pixels.

---


### Formation with Offset Velocities

A row of entities moving horizontally but each at a slightly higher speed than the previous:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((base-v 50)
        (increment 15))
    (world
      (entity 'e1
              (placement (* t base-v) 100)
              (shapes (circle 0 0 6 '#xFAEBD7)))
      (entity 'e2
              (placement (* t (+ base-v increment)) 180)
              (shapes (circle 0 0 6 '#xFFE4B5)))
      (entity 'e3
              (placement (* t (+ base-v (* 2 increment))) 260)
              (shapes (circle 0 0 6 '#xFFDAB9)))
      (entity 'e4
              (placement (* t (+ base-v (* 3 increment))) 340)
              (shapes (circle 0 0 6 '#xFFD7A3)))
      (entity 'e5
              (placement (* t (+ base-v (* 4 increment))) 420)
              (shapes (circle 0 0 6 '#xFFC478))))))
```

[VISUAL: Five peach-colored circles in horizontal rows, each row moving faster than the one above. The bottom row pulls ahead steadily.]

Velocity gradient: 50, 65, 80, 95, 110 px/s.

---


### Circular Velocity Field

Entities placed around a circle, each moving tangent to the circle:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((cx 240)
        (cy 240)
        (r 100)
        (n 6)
        (speed 60))
    (world
      (entity 'p0
              (let* ((angle 0.0)
                     (tx (- (sin angle)))
                     (ty (cos angle))
                     (x0 (+ cx (* r (cos angle))))
                     (y0 (+ cy (* r (sin angle)))))
                (placement (+ x0 (* t speed tx))
                           (+ y0 (* t speed ty))))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x444444)))
      (entity 'p1
              (let* ((angle 1.0472)
                     (tx (- (sin angle)))
                     (ty (cos angle))
                     (x0 (+ cx (* r (cos angle))))
                     (y0 (+ cy (* r (sin angle)))))
                (placement (+ x0 (* t speed tx))
                           (+ y0 (* t speed ty))))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x444444)))
      (entity 'p2
              (let* ((angle 2.0944)
                     (tx (- (sin angle)))
                     (ty (cos angle))
                     (x0 (+ cx (* r (cos angle))))
                     (y0 (+ cy (* r (sin angle)))))
                (placement (+ x0 (* t speed tx))
                           (+ y0 (* t speed ty))))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x444444)))
      (entity 'p3
              (let* ((angle 3.1416)
                     (tx (- (sin angle)))
                     (ty (cos angle))
                     (x0 (+ cx (* r (cos angle))))
                     (y0 (+ cy (* r (sin angle)))))
                (placement (+ x0 (* t speed tx))
                           (+ y0 (* t speed ty))))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x444444)))
      (entity 'p4
              (let* ((angle 4.1888)
                     (tx (- (sin angle)))
                     (ty (cos angle))
                     (x0 (+ cx (* r (cos angle))))
                     (y0 (+ cy (* r (sin angle)))))
                (placement (+ x0 (* t speed tx))
                           (+ y0 (* t speed ty))))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x444444)))
      (entity 'p5
              (let* ((angle 5.2360)
                     (tx (- (sin angle)))
                     (ty (cos angle))
                     (x0 (+ cx (* r (cos angle))))
                     (y0 (+ cy (* r (sin angle)))))
                (placement (+ x0 (* t speed tx))
                           (+ y0 (* t speed ty))))
              (shapes (circle 0 0 5 '#x444444))))))
```

[VISUAL: Six dark gray circles initially arranged in a hexagon around the center. Each moves tangent to the circle (perpendicular to the radius), creating a rotating velocity field effect.]

Each entity's velocity is tangent to the circle at its starting point. Over time, they drift away from the circle in straight lines.

