### Velocity Magnitude Encoding

Encode velocity magnitude as color brightness or size:

```scheme
(define (route t)
  (let ((v1 30)
        (v2 70)
        (v3 110)
        (v4 150))
    (world
      (entity 'slow
              (placement (* t v1) 100)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 4 '#x666666)))
      (entity 'medium-slow
              (placement (* t v2) 200)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 6 '#x999999)))
      (entity 'medium-fast
              (placement (* t v3) 300)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 8 '#xCCCCCC)))
      (entity 'fast
              (placement (* t v4) 400)
              (shapes
                (circle 0 0 10 '#xFFFFFF))))))
```

[VISUAL: Four circles moving left-to-right at increasing speeds. The slowest (top) is smallest and darkest; the fastest (bottom) is largest and brightest.]

Visual velocity cue: size and brightness correlate with speed.

